audioContentItems.fileTranscript: In this simulation we will determine the learning style of each person.
This is a screen navigational simulation. Follow the instructions provided throughout the simulation and complete the sym.

This is the Hotspot. You would need to click on it to type in the answer or you would need to click on it to move to the next step. After typing in the details, you would need to click the 'enter' key to move forward.
There are several types of learning, categorized based on theories, approaches, and settings. Here’s an overview

Visual learners understand best through pictures, charts, and diagrams. They prefer shapes and patterns over words or speech. Teachers can help by using tools like graphic organizers to explain ideas clearly.

Auditory learners learn best by hearing and speaking. They enjoy lectures, group discussions, and talking through ideas. They often figure things out by speaking first, rather than planning what to say.

Reading & writing learners understand best through words. They enjoy reading and do well with written tasks like stories or reports. They prefer learning through text, such as reading books or writing notes. Teachers can help by asking them to explain diagrams or charts in writing, which they can review later to remember the information.
Now let’s determine your learning style through a quick evaluation.

Kinesthetic learners learn best by doing. They like hands-on activities, real-life examples, and practicing skills through physical actions. Teachers can help by giving them practical tasks, like recreating experiments or working through examples to understand new ideas.
